This paper deals with information theory, networking, and coding theory, which are all subfields of computer science. The paper discusses the optimality of a decentralized coded caching scheme, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers the case of error-prone shared links, which is a networking problem (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper proposes an optimal error correcting delivery scheme, which involves coding theory (cs.SI). The paper also uses techniques from index coding, which is a subfield of computer science dealing with data compression and transmission (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the worst-case rate, which is a topic in complexity theory (cs.CC).
